Ozoni

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Broth
	•	600 ml (2½ cups) water
	•	4 g (1 tsp) dashi powder
	•	15 ml (1 tbsp) light soy sauce
	•	10 ml (2 tsp) mirin

Main Components
	•	120 g (4 oz) boneless chicken thigh, cut into 3 cm pieces
	•	2 pieces Japanese mochi
	•	40 g (1½ oz) spinach, trimmed and cut into 4 cm lengths

Allergen options:
	•	Use kombu-only dashi powder to remove fish allergen
	•	Substitute tamari for soy sauce if needed

⸻

Method
	1.	Prepare Broth
Heat water to about 80°C (not boiling). Remove from heat and whisk in dashi powder until fully dissolved and clear.
	2.	Cook Chicken
Return broth to gentle heat. Add chicken in a single layer and maintain a bare simmer for 6–7 minutes, until just cooked and broth remains clear.
	3.	Season
Add soy sauce and mirin. Stir gently and simmer 2 minutes to integrate flavors. Taste and adjust with a small splash of water if needed.
	4.	Toast Mochi
Toast mochi in a toaster oven, grill, or dry pan until puffed and lightly blistered with golden patches.
	5.	Assemble
Place toasted mochi in serving bowls. Ladle hot broth and chicken over mochi. Add spinach to the remaining broth for about 20 seconds until just wilted, then distribute and serve immediately.

⸻

Optional Refinements
	•	Grill mochi over charcoal for deeper aroma
	•	Finish with a pinch of yuzu zest for brightness
	•	Replace chicken with grilled hamachi for a coastal Chiba variation